original: Kjellberg, William Gibson, generalkonsul, Göteborg, f. 21/7/78 i Gbg av konsuln, grosish. Carl-August K. o. Eliza Gibson. G. 1. 04 m. Elsa Mark, d. 16; 2. 18 m. Adine von Geijer. Barn: Sven Roland f. 05, doc., bitr. överläk. v. Karol. sjukh., Jonas 08, prakt, läk., Upps., Carl Wilhelm 20, löjtn., pol. mag., anst. h. Scand. Airl. Sysl., Elisabeth 22, g. m. sityresm. f. Östads stift. kapt. frih. Jonas P. Al-strömer. — Agronomiex. v. Alnarp 99. Äg. av Margretebergs egend. 00-11 o. av Bryngenäs egend. fr. 11, verkst. dir. o. inneh. av Gustaf Melins A-B 12-19, inneh. av firma Wilson & Co. i Gbg m. dotterbok Wilsons A-B i Sthlm, Trelleborg, Malmö o. Wilsons Boråssped. A-B i Borås fr. 23. Finsk konsul 36-42, Fini. gen :konsid 47. RNO, RVO, KFinlLOhkl., KFinlVRO, FFr-K3lkl, RÖHT, FinliRKSM, FM pro ben. hum.
translated: Kjellberg, William Gibson, Consul General, Gothenburg, b. 21/7/78 in Gothenburg, son of the Consul, wholesaler Carl-August K. and Eliza Gibson. Married 1. 04 with Elsa Mark, deceased in 16; 2. 18 with Adine von Geijer. Children: Sven Roland b. 05, PhD, Assistant Chief Physician at Karolinska Hospital, Jonas b. 08, practicing physician in Uppsala, Carl Wilhelm b. 20, Lieutenant, political scientist, employed at Scandinavian Airlines System, Elisabeth b. 22, married to a city councilor from Östad, Captain Baron Jonas P. Alströmer. — Graduated from the Agricultural University in Alnarp in 99. Owner of Margretebergs Estate from 00-11 and Bryngenäs Estate from 11, Managing Director and owner of Gustaf Melin AB from 12-19, owner of Wilson & Co. in Gothenburg with daughter company Wilsons AB in Stockholm, Trelleborg, Malmö, and Wilsons Boråssped. AB in Borås from 23. Finnish consul from 36-42, Finnish Honorary Consul General from 47. Recipient of Order of the North Star, Order of Vasa, Cross of Liberty, Order of the White Rose of Finland, French Order of Academic Palms, Order of the Polar Star, Finnish Red Cross Medal of Merit, Swedish Order of Freemasons.
